comments: Bogdanovic (UTA) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
During the rebound, Gordon (DEN) and Niang (UTA) make clean ball contact as they pursue the loose ball.
Millsap (DEN) and Ingles (UTA) come together at the end of the drive and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Ingles' ability to make his intended pass.
Jokic (DEN) is retreating and absorbs the contact created by Bogdanovic (UTA) to his chest during the sideline drive.
Niang (UTA) commits a take foul on Rivers (DEN).
Millsap (DEN) establishes himself in Ingles' (UTA) path and incidental contact occurs as Ingles drifts forward after the release on his driving shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) dislodges Gobert (UTA) from his legally obtained position during the rebound.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a post position and does not restrict Gobert's (UTA) FOM or ability to defend the shot.
Clarkson (UTA) avoids making contact to Millsap's (DEN) arm during his driving shot attempt.

Ingles (UTA) creates the marginal contact with Porter Jr. (DEN) by extending his head into his body. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Rivers (DEN) moves laterally into and makes contact with Clarkson's (UTA) body, which affects his SQBR.
Rivers (DEN) commits a take foul on Bogdanovic (UTA).
Ingles (UTA) cleanly pokes the ball loose from Jokic (DEN) on the steal attempt.
